description: This file is a service worker script for Mock Service Worker (MSW), a library used for mocking API requests during development and testing. It sets up minimal event listeners for 'install', 'activate', and 'fetch' events to ensure the service worker is correctly registered and the mocking library can take control of fetch requests.

methods.name: install
methods.description: Handles the 'install' event to immediately activate the service worker using skipWaiting.

methods.name: activate
methods.description: Handles the 'activate' event to take control of all clients immediately.

methods.name: fetch
methods.description: Handles fetch events without processing them, allowing MSW to intercept requests later.
